FBIS3-48153 "dreas015_q_94002" FBIS-EAS-94-015 Document Type:Daily Report 25 Jan 1994 AUSTRALASIA Australia `Conditions' for Ties Outlined BK2001063494 Melbourne Radio Australia in English 0500 GMT 20 Jan 94 BK2001063494 Melbourne Radio Australia Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Acting Australian foreign affairs minister Gordon Bilney has confirmed North Korea has approached Australia about resuming normal diplomatic ties. Mr. Bilney says informal talks have been held recently in Southeast Asian capitals. Mr. Bilney says Australia has some requirements that must be met before relations can be resumed. [Begin Bilney recording] There are a number of conditions which the North Koreans would have to meet before we move any further along this track, including, explicitly, adherence to IAEA [International Atomic Energy Agency] safeguards with (?at the moment) of course the chairman of the IAEA board of governors, a resolution of the political [word indistinct] talks with the South Koreans, and progress in its relations with the United States. Those are three things. We are not acting alone. We are not going solo on any particular initiative with this and the DPRK. [end recording]
